    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An emulsion of asphalt cement and water, that contains a small amount of emulsifying agent. The amount of asphalt in emulsion will depend upon the grade and type, but is typically 55-65% by volume. Uses include surfacing floors, painting pipes, and waterproofing concrete walls.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
